items.title: Awesome Cl
items.content_text:
### Clojure

*   [Cloture (‚≠ê379)](https://github.com/ruricolist/cloture) - Clojure in Common Lisp.
*   [clj-con (‚≠ê40)](https://github.com/dtenny/clj-con) - Clojure-style concurrency operations in Common Lisp. [MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).
*   [clj-re (‚≠ê12)](https://github.com/dtenny/clj-re/) - Clojure-style regular expression functions.

### Typing

*   [typo (‚≠ê43)](https://github.com/marcoheisig/Typo/) -  A portable type inference library for Common Lisp. [MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).

### Others / OpenAPI, OData, OpenRPC

*   [apispec (‚≠ê34)](https://github.com/cxxxr/apispec) -  A Common Lisp library for handling Web API requests and responses. [BSD\_3Clause](https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/License:BSD_3Clause).
    *   takes an OpenAPI3 yaml specification and allows to validate and parse HTTP request headers, parameters and bodies.
*   [cl-odata-client (‚≠ê6)](https://github.com/copyleft/cl-odata-client) - Common Lisp client library for accessing [OData services](https://www.odata.org). [MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).
*   [OpenRPC (‚≠ê32)](https://github.com/40ants/openrpc) - OpenRPC implementation for Common Lisp. [BSD](https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/License:BSD_3Clause).
    *   Automatic OpenRPC spec generation
    *   Automatic JSON-RPC client building by OpenRPC spec. This includes creation of Common Lisp classes and methods for making RPC requests and returning native CL objects.
    *   all JSON marshalling is done under the hood.

### Apps / Third-party APIs

*   ‚≠ê [FiveAM (‚≠ê197)](https://github.com/sionescu/fiveam) - Simple regression testing framework. [FreeBSD](https://directory.fsf.org/wiki?title=License:FreeBSD).
    *   [FiveAM documentation](https://fiveam.common-lisp.dev/docs/index.html)
    *   [fiveam-matchers (‚≠ê9)](https://github.com/tdrhq/fiveam-matchers/) -  an extensible, composable matchers library for fiveam. [Apache2.0](https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/License:Apache2.0).
*   [testieren](https://cicadas.surf/cgit/colin/testiere.git/about/) - a testing utility where tests are included at the top of a `defun/t` form. They are run when you recompile your functions interactively. With mocking and stubbing support. [GPL3](http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html).

### Files and directories / Third-party APIs

*   [pathname-utils (‚≠ê13)](https://github.com/Shinmera/pathname-utils) - A collection of utilities to help with pathname operations. [zlib](https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/License:Zlib).
    *   [filesystem-utils (‚≠ê16)](https://github.com/Shinmera/filesystem-utils) - deal with common problems with filesystems, such as listing files, probing file types, determining default directories, etc.
    *   no dependencies, doesn't access the filesystem.
    *   [file-attributes (‚≠ê18)](https://github.com/Shinmera/file-attributes) -  access to common file attributes (uid, gid, permissions, ctime, mtime, atime).

### Macro helpers / Third-party APIs

*   [easy-macros (‚≠ê21)](https://github.com/tdrhq/easy-macros/) -  an easy way to write 90% of your macros. [Apache2.0](https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/License:Apache2.0).
*   [trivial-with-current-source-from (‚≠ê38)](https://github.com/scymtym/trivial-with-current-source-form/) - Helps macro writers produce better errors for macro users. [GPL3](http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html).
items.content_html:

  • Cloture (‚≠ê379) - Clojure in Common Lisp.
  • clj-con (‚≠ê40) - Clojure-style concurrency operations in Common Lisp. MIT.
  • clj-re (‚≠ê12) - Clojure-style regular expression functions.

Others / OpenAPI, OData, OpenRPC

  • apispec (‚≠ê34) - A Common Lisp library for handling Web API requests and responses. BSD_3Clause.
    • takes an OpenAPI3 yaml specification and allows to validate and parse HTTP request headers, parameters and bodies.
  • cl-odata-client (‚≠ê6) - Common Lisp client library for accessing OData services. MIT.
  • OpenRPC (‚≠ê32) - OpenRPC implementation for Common Lisp. BSD.
    • Automatic OpenRPC spec generation
    • Automatic JSON-RPC client building by OpenRPC spec. This includes creation of Common Lisp classes and methods for making RPC requests and returning native CL objects.
    • all JSON marshalling is done under the hood.

Apps / Third-party APIs

  • ‚≠ê FiveAM (‚≠ê197) - Simple regression testing framework. FreeBSD.
    • FiveAM documentation
    • fiveam-matchers (‚≠ê9) - an extensible, composable matchers library for fiveam. Apache2.0.
  • testieren - a testing utility where tests are included at the top of a defun/t form. They are run when you recompile your functions interactively. With mocking and stubbing support. GPL3.

Files and directories / Third-party APIs

  • pathname-utils (‚≠ê13) - A collection of utilities to help with pathname operations. zlib.
    • filesystem-utils (‚≠ê16) - deal with common problems with filesystems, such as listing files, probing file types, determining default directories, etc.
    • no dependencies, doesn't access the filesystem.
    • file-attributes (‚≠ê18) - access to common file attributes (uid, gid, permissions, ctime, mtime, atime).

Macro helpers / Third-party APIs

  • easy-macros (‚≠ê21) - an easy way to write 90% of your macros. Apache2.0.

    *   [Camera Preview (‚≠ê4)](https://github.com/tony-xlh/capacitor-plugin-camera-preview) - Access camera using Dynamsoft Camera Enhancer.
